The Nanyuki Teaching and Referral Hospital will receive Sh800 million machines from the national government, President Uhuru Kenyatta said on Monday.He said the hospital will be elevated to a fully fledged teaching facility. Uhuru spoke while commissioning medical equipment at the facility.He said the hospital will cater to patients from the neighbouring Meru, Isiolo, Samburu and Nyeri counties. &ldquo;Patients who used to seek medical services from as far as Nairobi will be getting them here. We also want to ease travel costs,&rdquo; Uhuru said. The President, Deputy President William Ruto, CSs and other guests were stopped in the town to address a crowd that had gathered in the streets, blocking their convoy.Uhuru, who was on a two-day tour of the Mt Kenya region, also launched construction of a renal unit at the Nanyuki Teaching and Referral Hospital and commissioned radiography equipment purchased by the state.